 ------------------------------------
 Guard.js - JavaScript API call validation library
 ------------------------------------

 About:
   Guard.js is a library which helps validating API calls in your library.
   
 Usage:
   myLibrary.myFunction	= function myFunction(sName, fHandler, bDirection) {
       // Validate arguments
       Guard(arguments, [
           ["name",      String],          // 'name' is required, must be string
           ["handler",   Function]         // 'handler' is required, must be function
           ["direction", Boolean, true]    // 'direction' is optional, if passed must be boolean
       ]);
       
       // Execute your library code here

   };
   
   >>> myLibrary.myFunction()
   >>> [Exception... Missing required 1st argument "name" in "myFunction" function call]
   
   >>> myLibrary.myFunction("test", true)
   >>> [Exception... Incompatible type of 2nd argument "handler" in "myFunction" function call]
   
   >>> myLibrary.myFunction("test", null)
   >>> [Exception... null is not allowed value of 2nd argument "handler" in "myFunction" function call]
   